quran[6]{c,v,t}:
  4,71,"O you who believe! Take your precautions, and either go forward in parties or go forward all together"
  4,72,"There are certainly among you men, he who would fall behind: If a misfortune befalls you, he says: \"Allah did favor me because I was not present with them"
  4,73,"But if good fortune comes to you from Allah, he would be sure to say— As if there were no affection between you and him— \"Oh! I wish I had been with them; A fine thing should I then have made of it"
  4,74,"Let those (people) fight in the cause of Allah, (those) who sell the life of this world for the Hereafter. To him who fights in the cause of Allah— Whether he is slain or gets victory— Soon We shall give him a reward that is Great"
  4,75,"And what is wrong with you (believers) not to fight in the cause of Allah, those (believers) who, are weak, the ill-treated (and oppressed)? Men, women, and children, the cry is: \"Our Lord! Rescue us from this town, whose people are oppressors; And from You give us a guardian who will protect; And from You give us one who will help"
  4,76,"Those who believe, fight in the cause of Allah and those who reject Faith (and) fight in the cause of Evil: So you fight against the friends of Satan: Weak indeed is the cunning of Satan"